AIM: The aim of this report is to describe the restorative treatment of an 
18-year-old patient diagnosed with autosomal recessive hypocalcified-hypoplastic 
amelogenesis imperfecta (AI).
BACKGROUND: Esthetic and functional rehabilitations in AI cases are challenging 
and should consider individual aspects, such as age, socioeconomic status, AI 
type, and intraoral condition.
REPORT: AI was diagnosed in an 18-year-old patient.
