expectancy, minimal invasiveness, amount of treatment time required, and lower 
costs, oral rehabilitation with overdentures provided an adequate functional and 
esthetic rehabilitation of the patient.
CLINICAL SIGNIFICANCE: This report demonstrated overdentures to be a viable, 
relatively inexpensive, and non-invasive treatment choice of a patient with AI 
with concerns about treatment longevity, invasiveness, cost, esthetics, and 
long-term maintenance.

